    <item>
      <title>Tutorial: String Manipulation in Perl with s///, y///, and s///g</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/perl-rename-tutorial/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/perl-rename-tutorial/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Perl provides powerful operators for manipulating strings using regular expressions. Here&amp;rsquo;s a breakdown of each operator with examples:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;s-substitution-operator&#34;&gt;s/// (Substitution Operator)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Syntax:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;s/old-pattern/new-pattern/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; Replaces occurrences of &lt;code&gt;old-pattern&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;new-pattern&lt;/code&gt; in a string.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;s/John/Doe/&lt;/code&gt; replaces the first instance of &amp;ldquo;John&amp;rdquo; with &amp;ldquo;Doe&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example 1: Replace &amp;ldquo;John&amp;rdquo; with &amp;ldquo;Doe&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;text = &amp;#34;Hello John. John is a friend.&amp;#34;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;regex = s/John/Doe/;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Result: &amp;#34;Hello Doe. John is a friend.&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example 2: Replace &amp;ldquo;white&amp;rdquo; with &amp;ldquo;black&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
